The paper deals with a problem in computer vision, specifically semantic segmentation, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel learning model using sparse optimization, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of user-tagged images from media-sharing sites such as Flickr suggests a potential application in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the problem of noisy labels is a common issue in natural language processing (cs.CL), which could also be relevant to this paper.
